Function: alisinv
Section: algebras
C-Name: alisinv
Prototype: iGGD&
Help: alisinv(al,x,{&ix}): tests whether x is invertible and sets ix to the
 inverse of x.
Doc: Given an element $x$ in \var{al}, tests whether $x$ is invertible, and sets
 $ix$ to the inverse of $x$.
 \bprog
 ? A = alinit(nfinit(y), [-1,1]);
 ? alisinv(A,[-1,1]~)
 %2 = 0
 ? alisinv(A,[1,2]~,&ix)
 %3 = 1
 ? ix
 %4 = [Mod(Mod(-1/3, y), x^2 + 1), Mod(Mod(2/3, y), x^2 + 1)]~
 @eprog
